=Silk Road 絲綢之路=
translation of the German term "Seidentraßen" coined by [[Ferdinand von Richthofen]]

==Literature==
===Exhibition Catalogues===
* Annette L. Juliano and Judith A. Lerner: Monks and merchants : Silk Road treasures from Northwest China ; Gansu and Ningxia, 4th - 7th century ; [publ. on the occasion of the exhibition "Monks and merchants: Silk Road treasures from Northwest China", Asia Society Museum of Art, Palm Beach, Florida, february 9 - april 21, 2002]. New York: Abrams, 2001.
* Victor Mair: Secrets of the Silk Road - an exhibition of discoveries from the Xinjiang Uyghur Autonomous Region, China. Santa Ana, California: Bowers Museum, 2010